1	//axhob_operation
2	{rbtgo_retriever_invest}
3	
4	NOTE: This operation invests a
5	{rbtr_retriever}
6	{giam_service_account}
7	into the
8	{rbtgi_depot_project}
9	with read-only
10	{rbtgi_repository}
11	access.
12	The
13	{rbtr_governor}
14	mints the SA, generates its credential key, and writes the RBRA bytes to the assay output slot.
15	The operation is identity-parameterized: a required identity folio (param1) is supplied by the operator; the SA account name is composed as `${RBCC_account_retriever}-<identity>`.
16	Fatal if the SA already exists — operator must
17	{rbtgo_retriever_divest}
18	first to re-key.
19	
20	//axhos_step
21	. *Authenticate as
22	{rbtr_governor}*:
23	.. Execute
24	{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
25	.. {rbbc_store}
26	`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
27	
28	//axhos_step
29	. *Compose
30	{rbtr_retriever}
31	Service Account Identity*:
32	.. {rbbc_require}
33	identity folio (param1) is non-empty
34	.. {rbbc_store}
35	`«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»` as `${RBCC_account_retriever}-<identity>` (operator-supplied identity composing the account name)
36	.. {rbbc_store}
37	`«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` as `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»@${RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID}.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
38	.. NOTE: `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID` is derived from `(RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER)` at regime kindle time; no operator-supplied project ID field is referenced.
39	
40	//axhos_step
41	. *Preflight: Confirm Service Account Does Not Exist*:
42	.. {rbbc_call}
43	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
44	.. {rbbc_fatal}
45	if HTTP 200: service account already exists — operator must execute
46	{rbtgo_retriever_divest}
47	before re-investing this role
48	.. {rbbc_require}
49	HTTP 404 to proceed
50	
51	//axhos_step
52	. *Create
53	{rbtr_retriever}
54	Service Account*:
55	.. {rbbc_call}
56	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
57	... accountId: `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»`
58	... displayName: `Recipe Bottle Retriever (<identity>)`
59	... description: `Read-only access to Google Artifact Registry - identity: <identity>`
60	... project:
61	{rbtgi_depot_project}
62	.. {rbbc_require}
63	HTTP 200 response
64	.. {rbbc_store}
65	`«RETRIEVER_UNIQUE_ID»` from response `.uniqueId` field
66	
67	//axhos_step
68	. *Verify Service Account Propagation*:
69	.. {rbbc_call}
70	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
71	.. {rbbc_poll}
72	with backoff until HTTP 200 (newly-created SA may not be immediately resolvable by email)
73	.. NOTE: Poll must use the email address, not the numeric ID. The email-based lookup path has independent propagation from the UID-based path, and subsequent steps (keys.list, keys.create) all use the email address. Polling by UID can succeed while the email path still returns 404.
74	.. {rbbc_require}
75	service account accessible by email
76	
77	//axhos_step
78	. *Preflight: Ensure Pristine Key State*:
79	.. {rbbc_call}
80	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/list[serviceAccounts.keys.list] for `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
81	.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
82	.. NOTE: Keys subresource read-path may lag SA email-path readiness — the SA GET probe (previous step) can return 200 while `keys.list` on the same email immediately returns 404, observed as a non-monotonic 200→200→404 flap on freshly-minted depots. The 404 confirms `keys.list` returned no state, making retry safe. Shares budget with step 7 keys.create — same underlying physics (subresource visibility after parent creation). See `Memos/memo-20260514-pristine-gauntlet-iam-flap.md` for transcript evidence and <<rbscip_iam_propagation>> for the doctrinal pattern.
83	.. {rbbc_store}
84	`«EXISTING_KEYS»` from response `.keys[]`
85	.. {rbbc_require}
86	no keys with `keyType: USER_MANAGED` exist
87	.. {rbbc_fatal}
88	if USER_MANAGED keys found: "Manual cleanup required via Console"
89	
90	//axhos_step
91	. *Generate Service Account Key*:
92	.. {rbbc_call}
93	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create] for `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` with:
